00:32.100 --> 00:35.140
(winding)
(metallic tapping)

00:36.770 --> 00:38.770
(slow music)

00:40.274 --> 00:42.314
(light music)

01:12.506 --> 01:14.176
(ding!)

01:15.809 --> 01:17.679
(music)

01:36.664 --> 01:38.534
(whinnying)

01:44.538 --> 01:46.708
(ding!)

01:50.010 --> 01:52.210
(music fading)

01:53.181 --> 01:56.121
- Hands above the covers!
- Oh!

01:59.820 --> 02:03.460
- Was I...? It wasn't you.
It was the dreaming you.

02:03.524 --> 02:05.094
Keep your "yous" separate

02:05.159 --> 02:08.729
and you'll never have anything
to apologize for, possum.

02:10.198 --> 02:12.798
So what shall we girls
tackle today?

02:12.866 --> 02:15.296
- I wanna make muffins.

02:15.369 --> 02:17.869
- Well, wash up and we'll see.

02:18.872 --> 02:20.742
- Oh!

02:23.377 --> 02:25.877
(sighing in contentment)

02:26.947 --> 02:28.747
(soft music)

02:35.656 --> 02:37.426
(birdsong)

02:39.760 --> 02:41.660
(soft music)

02:47.401 --> 02:52.111
Oh... We don't have any vanilla,
do we?

02:52.172 --> 02:54.612
- No. Make them without.

02:54.675 --> 02:56.505
- Uh... but...

02:56.577 --> 02:58.777
the book says we need it.

02:58.846 --> 03:01.216
They won't turn out
the way they're supposed to.

03:01.282 --> 03:04.752
- Most things in life don't turn
out the way they're supposed to.

03:04.818 --> 03:07.718
In fact, that will be today's
lesson:

03:07.788 --> 03:09.588
Anticipointment.

03:09.657 --> 03:11.827
- Oh! Fun!

03:11.892 --> 03:15.302
- When we expect too much
out of life,

03:15.363 --> 03:17.733
we get smacked
by disappointment.

03:17.798 --> 03:19.228
- Oh.

03:19.300 --> 03:21.470
- Words to live by.

03:25.239 --> 03:27.309
(soft music)

03:39.853 --> 03:41.493
(ding!)

03:45.793 --> 03:47.233
(sighing)

03:47.295 --> 03:50.755
Why can't you leave them at
the back of the church on Sunday

03:50.831 --> 03:53.071
and people can grab them
when they leave?

03:53.133 --> 03:55.243
- Because they're warm now.

03:55.303 --> 03:58.073
People have been so kind to us.

03:58.138 --> 04:00.708
It's time we repay them.

04:00.774 --> 04:03.244
- But so many of them haven't.

04:03.311 --> 04:05.781
- But so many of them have.

04:05.846 --> 04:07.676
I won't be long.

04:09.983 --> 04:11.853
I won't be long.

04:14.154 --> 04:16.423
- Fine.

04:16.490 --> 04:18.390
But head down at all times,

04:18.459 --> 04:20.988
and whatever words
come out of their mouths

04:21.060 --> 04:22.931
are not to be listened to.

04:22.996 --> 04:24.866
- Yes, Mum.

04:24.932 --> 04:26.602
I'm 24.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.597
- Well, if you want to see 25,

04:28.669 --> 04:32.269
you'll come back as soon
as they snatch that last muffin.

04:32.340 --> 04:34.940
(young woman sighing)
- Deal.

04:35.008 --> 04:36.878
There and back.

04:37.878 --> 04:39.548
Mwah!

04:40.348 --> 04:42.378
(giggling)

04:56.364 --> 04:58.404
(winding)

04:59.733 --> 05:01.103
(ticking)

05:01.168 --> 05:02.968
(soft music)

05:03.036 --> 05:04.966
(birdsong)

05:05.038 --> 05:07.408
(light, upbeat music)

05:41.875 --> 05:45.005
- Oh, Claire!
What a treat seeing you.

05:45.078 --> 05:47.008
I'm surprised you're out.

05:47.080 --> 05:49.920
- I couldn't keep these
to myself.

05:50.951 --> 05:52.921
- Oh.

05:52.986 --> 05:55.016
They smell amazing!

05:55.088 --> 05:57.018
Thank you, Claire.

05:57.090 --> 05:58.690
- Anytime!

05:58.759 --> 06:01.029
- Oh, so she's okay,
your mother?

06:01.094 --> 06:02.764
- Better than ever.

06:02.830 --> 06:06.170
- Oh, she's very lucky
to have you, you know.

06:06.233 --> 06:08.843
- I'd do anything for her.

06:08.902 --> 06:12.542
- I wish my children were here
to take care of me.

06:12.606 --> 06:15.436
Too busy complicating
their own lives

06:15.509 --> 06:17.809
to realize where they're needed.

06:17.878 --> 06:22.278
When my husband died,
I was at his bedside,

06:22.349 --> 06:25.219
holding a picture
of our children.

06:25.285 --> 06:27.755
Oh, well,
she's just lucky, is all.

06:27.821 --> 06:30.221
Thank you for the muffin,
Claire.

06:30.290 --> 06:32.430
- My pleasure!
- Oh!

06:34.428 --> 06:36.128
Have a great day.

06:36.196 --> 06:37.796
- You, too.

06:37.865 --> 06:40.795
(giggling)
- Off I go!

06:40.868 --> 06:42.838
(chuckling)

06:51.011 --> 06:52.411
- Yes?
- Hi.

06:52.480 --> 06:54.650
Are your parents home?

06:54.715 --> 06:56.545
(woman): Who is it, baby?

06:56.617 --> 06:59.047
- It's that girl
from down the street.

06:59.119 --> 07:01.249
- Shhh.
Stay quiet and she'll leave.

07:01.321 --> 07:04.961
- I don't like her.
How could you? She's crazy.

07:05.025 --> 07:06.685
Now shhh.

07:09.963 --> 07:12.603
- Mom?
(muffled screaming)

07:12.666 --> 07:15.796
(crying)
- Stay off my damn porch!!

07:18.138 --> 07:20.768
(brakes screeching)
(exclaiming)

07:20.841 --> 07:24.041
- Stay home, freak show!
(Claire crying)

07:33.186 --> 07:35.056
- Are you okay?

07:37.858 --> 07:40.628
Oh, my... give me your arm.

07:40.694 --> 07:42.304
- Oh...
(grunting)

07:42.362 --> 07:44.202
Oh...

07:46.534 --> 07:48.904
- Come on, let's get you inside.

07:56.910 --> 07:58.310
- Hey...

07:58.378 --> 08:00.648
it's 14108 Pinewood.

08:00.714 --> 08:04.284
- Well, yeah.
- I have a muffin for here.

08:04.351 --> 08:06.221
- I'm sure you do.

08:07.220 --> 08:08.860
Oh, crap.

08:08.922 --> 08:10.392
Here.

08:11.191 --> 08:14.361
Hold your nose like this.
- Oh.

08:14.427 --> 08:16.657
- Go sit inside.
- Okay.

08:21.201 --> 08:25.111
- Well, it looks like you've got
everything under control here.

08:26.239 --> 08:28.039
- Who's that?

08:28.108 --> 08:29.938
She's gorgeous.

08:33.080 --> 08:34.409
- No one.

08:34.481 --> 08:37.621
You should still
probably ice that.

08:37.684 --> 08:41.044
- Okay. May I see your room?

08:41.121 --> 08:43.160
- Uh... I guess.

08:43.222 --> 08:46.893
Just don't bleed on shit.
- I have a tampon up my nose.

08:46.960 --> 08:49.600
- Yeah, I can see that.

08:49.663 --> 08:52.133
(funky music)
(woman moaning)

08:53.200 --> 08:54.530
(moaning)

08:54.602 --> 08:56.372
Oh...

08:56.436 --> 08:58.636
Churn me like butter.

08:58.706 --> 09:03.076
You're my favourite cousin!

09:03.143 --> 09:05.713
Ah!! Ah!!

09:05.779 --> 09:07.919
(exclaiming)

09:10.283 --> 09:12.093
- Wow!

09:12.152 --> 09:14.152
I love this.

09:14.955 --> 09:18.185
I'm only allowed
to put up things that I create.

09:18.258 --> 09:21.798
- That's cool.
That's really cool.

09:21.862 --> 09:24.702
- I want a map like that.

09:24.765 --> 09:28.235
Have you been
to all those places?

09:29.369 --> 09:32.469
- My uncle's been
to all the pins that are red.

09:33.440 --> 09:37.310
All the blue pins are the places
I'm gonna get to someday.

09:41.882 --> 09:44.252
- Do you have anymore ice?

09:44.317 --> 09:46.187
- Yeah, sure, one second.

09:56.129 --> 09:58.599
(door opening)
(man): I'm home!

09:58.666 --> 10:01.266
- In the kitchen.
I have someone over.

10:01.334 --> 10:03.674
- Oh?

10:03.737 --> 10:06.267
Oh, it's you. Hello, Claire.

10:06.339 --> 10:08.509
- Hello, Pastor Paul.

10:08.575 --> 10:10.275
- You... you okay there?

10:11.679 --> 10:13.779
- Oh, I... I ran into a tree.

10:13.847 --> 10:16.277
- Well, I hope
you taught it a lesson.

10:16.349 --> 10:18.349
(laughing)

10:21.321 --> 10:23.961
You know, Claire, your mom's
probably worried sick.

10:24.024 --> 10:26.494
Let me drive you home.
- That would be swell.

10:26.559 --> 10:30.029
- Danielle, I'm gonna
give your friend a ride home!

10:30.097 --> 10:31.967
You wanna come with?!
- Nah.

10:32.032 --> 10:35.302
- We can stop and get
some chicken on the way home!

10:35.368 --> 10:37.638
- No, Paul.
- Oh...

10:37.705 --> 10:40.065
(chuckling)
Let's go Claire.

10:40.140 --> 10:42.080
- Okay. Ah...

10:45.879 --> 10:48.649
What's your favourite bird?

10:48.716 --> 10:51.916
- My favourite bird?
I've, uh...

10:52.886 --> 10:54.986
...never really given it
much thought.

10:55.055 --> 10:57.185
(chuckling)
Ugh, pigeon.

10:57.257 --> 10:58.987
No.

10:59.059 --> 11:00.389
Seagull.

11:00.460 --> 11:01.930
- Why?

11:01.995 --> 11:04.525
- I don't know. You?

11:05.365 --> 11:08.865
- I don't have one.
Birds scare me.

11:08.936 --> 11:11.966
- Birds scare your mom, Claire.

11:14.574 --> 11:16.584
Listen, um...

11:16.643 --> 11:18.883
Okay - ahem - how would you...

11:18.946 --> 11:23.346
like to represent the parish
at the annual...

11:23.416 --> 11:26.886
Pump Up the Jamboree
Youth Ministry Conference?

11:28.922 --> 11:31.592
- Why me?
= Because you'd be perfect.

11:31.658 --> 11:34.688
And - ahem - it would be a sin

11:34.762 --> 11:37.502
to turn something like this
down.

11:37.564 --> 11:39.434
- Oh, wow.

11:42.435 --> 11:44.635
I... I... couldn't.

11:44.704 --> 11:46.874
- Yes, you could. And you will.

11:46.940 --> 11:49.340
Even if your mother
doesn't agree.

11:49.409 --> 11:50.839
- Can she come?

11:50.911 --> 11:53.451
- No, Claire, she can't.

11:53.513 --> 11:55.723
- Oh.

11:55.783 --> 11:58.023
Will you be there?

11:58.786 --> 12:01.886
- Definitely.
- Then yes.

12:01.955 --> 12:05.455
Yes, I'm going to come.

12:05.525 --> 12:06.985
- Excellent.

12:07.060 --> 12:09.160
Well, then it's settled.

12:10.330 --> 12:12.470
You still live
at your grandparents' house?

12:12.532 --> 12:15.702
- It's ours now.
- Oh?

12:15.769 --> 12:18.939
- They signed everything over.

12:19.006 --> 12:22.236
- You ever go visit them?
- It's too far.

12:22.309 --> 12:25.049
- Fifty miles is not far,
Claire.

12:25.112 --> 12:27.752
- That's a world away.

12:27.815 --> 12:29.875
- Well...

12:29.950 --> 12:32.950
here... we... are.

12:38.125 --> 12:40.355
- Thank you, Pastor Paul.

12:41.128 --> 12:42.658
- You're welcome, Claire.
And, um...

12:42.729 --> 12:45.029
would you do me a favour?
Would you...

12:45.098 --> 12:47.868
say hello to your mom for me?

12:47.935 --> 12:49.795
- I always do.
- Thanks.

12:51.004 --> 12:53.374
- Okay, bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

12:58.678 --> 13:01.078
(knocking)
Jesus Christ!

13:04.517 --> 13:05.917
Yes?

13:05.986 --> 13:08.516
- I forgot to offer you
my muffin.

13:08.588 --> 13:11.258
I made it nice and moist
for you.

13:11.324 --> 13:14.494
I even got
the neighbour's zucchini in it.

13:15.195 --> 13:17.595
- Thank you, Claire. That's...

13:17.664 --> 13:19.904
Thank you.

13:21.701 --> 13:22.941
- Okay.
- Okay.

13:23.003 --> 13:26.673
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye. Oh, uh, Claire?

13:26.739 --> 13:29.139
I think, uh, the bleeding has...

13:29.209 --> 13:30.639
stopped.

13:30.710 --> 13:33.180
- Thanks.

13:33.246 --> 13:34.506
Bye-bye.

13:34.581 --> 13:36.421
- Bye-bye.

13:37.517 --> 13:39.417
(soft music)

13:54.067 --> 13:55.837
(sniffling)

13:55.903 --> 13:57.843
(soft music)

13:57.905 --> 13:59.665
(sighing)

13:59.739 --> 14:01.569
(sniffling)

14:04.912 --> 14:06.852
(sniffling)

14:24.497 --> 14:26.297
- Oh...

14:27.767 --> 14:30.337
Oh! They loved them!

14:30.403 --> 14:32.313
They loved them!

14:37.744 --> 14:39.984
(soft music)

15:19.519 --> 15:21.749
Oh! Hey!!
(honking)

15:21.821 --> 15:24.661
(screaming)
(gasping)

15:24.724 --> 15:26.564
- No! No!!

15:26.626 --> 15:29.856
No! Look what you did,
you idiot!

15:29.929 --> 15:32.399
- Uh, is it okay?

15:32.465 --> 15:35.765
- No, it's not okay! You're
gonna have to replace this!

15:35.835 --> 15:38.005
It's a fucking vintage camera!

15:38.071 --> 15:39.671
- I have glue.

15:41.541 --> 15:43.681
- Go. Just go!

15:43.743 --> 15:45.613
- Uh...

15:45.678 --> 15:47.108
I feel bad.

15:47.180 --> 15:50.480
- You should.
- Well, I... I do.

15:50.550 --> 15:52.120
- Good.

15:52.185 --> 15:54.385
- It was a mistake.

15:54.454 --> 15:55.724
- Just like you!

15:58.391 --> 16:00.391
(crying)

16:02.996 --> 16:05.026
(sobbing)

16:06.299 --> 16:09.199
(birdsong)
- ...and with that...

16:09.269 --> 16:13.269
comes a huge degree
of responsibility.

16:13.340 --> 16:18.510
Now, we often think of ourselves
are scions of free will,

16:18.578 --> 16:20.078
of...

16:20.147 --> 16:21.807
choice, of...

16:21.881 --> 16:23.681
personal desire.

16:23.750 --> 16:25.990
Now, that simply isn't the case.

16:26.053 --> 16:28.123
Every moment we experience

16:28.188 --> 16:31.818
contains not only a series
of consequences,

16:31.891 --> 16:36.401
but is also the product
of a predetermined blueprint

16:36.463 --> 16:39.603
set out for us by our Good Lord.

16:39.666 --> 16:43.266
Now, as much
as we want to fight the notion,

16:43.336 --> 16:46.036
nothing in this life is random.

16:46.106 --> 16:47.666
Each situation we encounter

16:47.740 --> 16:51.980
brings us closer to the truth
of our existence.

16:52.045 --> 16:54.075
And it is our responsibility

16:54.147 --> 16:57.347
to suffer the consequences
of our actions.

16:58.585 --> 17:00.015
Now thank you.

17:00.087 --> 17:03.017
Thank you for coming
and God bless.

17:03.756 --> 17:06.126
(doorbell ringing)

17:09.262 --> 17:11.531
- So how do I get you
a new one?

17:11.598 --> 17:13.028
- What, my camera?

17:13.099 --> 17:14.670
It's no use.

17:14.733 --> 17:17.844
- No.
I have a responsibility to you,

17:17.904 --> 17:20.114
and to fixing your camera.

17:20.173 --> 17:22.042
- Yeah, yeah, you do.

17:22.108 --> 17:24.479
- So what do I do?

17:25.278 --> 17:26.678
- The store's closed today.

17:26.746 --> 17:28.776
I'll meet you at your place
tomorrow.

17:28.848 --> 17:30.448
You can hook me up then.

17:30.517 --> 17:32.117
- What time?
- Say 10:00?

17:32.185 --> 17:34.285
- And how much money do I need?

17:34.354 --> 17:36.394
- Fifty bucks,
but bring more to be safe.

17:36.456 --> 17:38.786
- Deal.
- Deal.

17:38.858 --> 17:42.628
And hey. Your muffin
was freakin' delicious.

17:42.695 --> 17:46.325
- That was for your dad.
- I'll see ya tomorrow.

17:51.070 --> 17:54.970
- I said hello, Mum! Mum?

17:55.041 --> 17:57.511
- Not now, Claire.

17:58.811 --> 18:01.211
This is pointless.

18:01.281 --> 18:03.121
- Do you need a hand?

18:03.983 --> 18:05.753
Mum?

18:05.818 --> 18:07.718
- Do you call this clean?

18:07.787 --> 18:09.387
- It looks clean.

18:09.456 --> 18:12.086
- Well, it isn't.
- Mum...

18:12.159 --> 18:15.229
tomorrow I have to fix
something I broke.

18:15.295 --> 18:17.325
- What did you break, honey?

18:17.397 --> 18:19.297
- Someone's camera.

18:20.099 --> 18:22.639
It's my responsibility.

18:22.702 --> 18:24.572
- Your responsibility...

18:24.637 --> 18:28.067
is to our family and this home.

18:28.141 --> 18:31.641
Anything else is self-serving...

18:32.812 --> 18:35.822
...and I won't allow it
under this roof.

18:38.185 --> 18:40.215
- Are you okay, Mum?

18:40.287 --> 18:42.217
- It's disgusting.

18:43.190 --> 18:44.920
It's filthy.

18:44.991 --> 18:47.731
- The sermon was great, Mum.

18:47.794 --> 18:49.404
- Not now, Claire.

19:02.875 --> 19:04.875
(celestial music)

19:09.682 --> 19:13.322
- It is our responsibility
to suffer the consequences

19:13.386 --> 19:15.416
of our actions.

19:19.392 --> 19:21.162
(engine stalling)

19:21.228 --> 19:22.798
(sighing)

19:22.862 --> 19:26.172
- When was the last time
you used this thing?

19:26.233 --> 19:28.343
(engine stalling)

19:28.401 --> 19:30.171
Did you hear that?

19:30.237 --> 19:31.897
- No.

19:33.240 --> 19:36.080
(engine stalling, then starting)

19:36.876 --> 19:40.306
I don't know about this.
- This was your idea.

19:40.380 --> 19:43.850
I thought you wanted
to do the right thing.

19:43.916 --> 19:46.646
- I do. I do.

19:46.719 --> 19:50.619
I just... I've... I've...
never taken her car before.

19:52.425 --> 19:54.555
- We'll be back in no time.

19:54.627 --> 19:55.757
- Okay.

19:55.828 --> 19:58.998
I have to be back
before the timer goes off.

19:59.065 --> 20:00.695
- Uh...

20:00.767 --> 20:02.537
alright.

20:04.237 --> 20:06.237
(radio): Residents are asked
to keep an eye out

20:06.306 --> 20:07.836
for the alleged sex offender
whom,

20:07.907 --> 20:09.877
as a result of last Wednesday,
some are now calling

20:09.942 --> 20:13.152
the Diddler on the Roof.
The man is described as--

20:13.212 --> 20:14.652
- Gross.

20:14.714 --> 20:17.284
- So how long
is this gonna take?

20:17.350 --> 20:19.090
- Not long.

20:19.151 --> 20:20.891
- Stop.

20:22.121 --> 20:24.661
Stop!
- What?

20:36.135 --> 20:38.165
(seatbelt clicking)

20:38.237 --> 20:40.307
- Okay. Drive...

20:40.373 --> 20:42.073
Jeeves!

20:42.141 --> 20:44.281
- Okay, freak.

20:44.344 --> 20:47.214
- Gas levels acceptable,
Captain?

20:47.280 --> 20:51.080
- Assuming the gauge works,
we're at a quarter of a tank.

20:51.150 --> 20:53.490
- Attagirl! Eyes on the road.

20:53.953 --> 20:56.123
(radio): Another casualty
of the power outages

20:56.188 --> 20:58.828
from last month
was the local sperm bank.

20:58.891 --> 21:02.761
Due to their freezers not being
able to run at full efficiency,

21:02.829 --> 21:05.729
there was an estimated loss
of four-quadrillion sperm.

21:05.798 --> 21:07.928
We were able to find...
- This is weird.

21:08.000 --> 21:10.440
Can we listen to something else?

21:10.503 --> 21:13.213
- What do you wanna listen to?

21:13.272 --> 21:14.812
- Sound of the wind.

21:14.874 --> 21:17.814
- He's asking all male locals
to donate today.

21:17.877 --> 21:19.547
- Yay!

21:23.182 --> 21:25.722
(light music)
Ah...!

21:25.785 --> 21:27.385
Ah...

21:35.227 --> 21:37.297
(music)

22:00.387 --> 22:02.417
(ticking)

22:18.771 --> 22:20.611
(ding!)

22:27.947 --> 22:29.617
(knocking)

22:30.750 --> 22:33.420
- Hey, I gotta step out
for a moment

22:33.486 --> 22:35.186
to finalize
some Jamboree planning.

22:35.254 --> 22:37.364
Um... Tsk.

22:37.424 --> 22:40.164
Look... Danielle, uh...

22:40.226 --> 22:44.196
I would really like to sit down
and talk with you tonight.

22:44.263 --> 22:46.633
I... I found another bottle.

22:53.072 --> 22:55.782
Okay, well,
if you're ignoring me,

22:55.842 --> 22:58.012
then you probably won't hear

22:58.077 --> 23:01.977
that I left some money for food
on the fridge.

23:03.315 --> 23:05.815
- O...kay.

23:06.819 --> 23:08.559
Uh...

23:12.258 --> 23:13.458
- What's wrong?

23:13.526 --> 23:16.256
- I don't like this.

23:16.328 --> 23:18.258
- We're almost there.

23:18.330 --> 23:20.070
- Pull over.

23:20.132 --> 23:21.702
Pull over!

23:21.768 --> 23:24.898
Pull over. Pull... pull over.
Pull over.

23:24.971 --> 23:26.511
- Okay.

23:29.141 --> 23:31.141
Pull over. Pull over.

23:32.144 --> 23:33.614
Pull over.

23:33.680 --> 23:36.420
(Claire panting)
- Oh, my God, what?!

23:36.483 --> 23:38.853
(exclaiming)

23:40.186 --> 23:42.956
(exclaiming)

23:51.498 --> 23:53.428
(groaning)

24:04.511 --> 24:07.051
(Claire taking deep breaths)

24:08.180 --> 24:10.420
Are you okay?

24:10.483 --> 24:12.453
- Oh...

24:12.519 --> 24:15.189
Oh... I don't know.

24:17.189 --> 24:19.529
- Well... are you hungry?

24:19.592 --> 24:22.632
Did you eat anything today?

24:22.695 --> 24:25.055
- I'm always hungry.

24:47.386 --> 24:50.156
Mmm... good sandwich.

24:50.222 --> 24:52.222
Thanks. It's lettuce.

24:52.291 --> 24:54.331
- It's really good.

24:54.393 --> 24:56.103
- Good.

24:57.564 --> 24:59.234
- Mmm.

25:03.736 --> 25:06.336
- Hey, so, like...

25:06.405 --> 25:08.605
what's the deal with your mom?

25:08.675 --> 25:11.105
You know, like,
what's her thing?

25:12.545 --> 25:14.505
- What do you mean?

25:14.581 --> 25:16.781
She's... wonderful.

25:17.917 --> 25:20.187
- Dude, she keeps you locked up.

25:20.252 --> 25:22.222
- No, she doesn't.

25:23.255 --> 25:25.725
I chose to be home-schooled.

25:26.926 --> 25:29.596
- Let me at least
sit on your face

25:29.662 --> 25:32.362
if you're gonna go
all Pinocchio on me.

25:32.431 --> 25:34.471
(laughing)
- Gross.

25:34.533 --> 25:36.073
- I'm not judging.

25:36.135 --> 25:38.965
I'm just observing
with intense criticism.

25:40.607 --> 25:42.337
Like...

25:42.408 --> 25:44.538
like, what do you think
she's feeling right now,

25:44.611 --> 25:46.381
the fact
that you just took her car?

25:46.445 --> 25:48.145
Seriously?

25:50.082 --> 25:52.992
- I'm sure she's fine.
- Claire.

25:54.987 --> 25:56.457
- She is.

25:57.256 --> 26:00.656
- If you haven't noticed,
I'm not a fan of lying.

26:03.295 --> 26:04.995
- Okay, okay.

26:06.966 --> 26:09.896
She's probably
balling her face off.

26:09.969 --> 26:12.299
(sighing)
- Claire, that's insane.

26:12.371 --> 26:15.911
You are just taking your friend
to the next town over

26:15.975 --> 26:20.005
to buy her a new camera
from the one that you broke.

26:20.813 --> 26:23.583
What?
- You said friend!

26:23.650 --> 26:25.420
(Danielle snorting)
- Okay, okay,

26:25.484 --> 26:27.654
we're not going all that.

26:27.720 --> 26:30.420
Let's go.
We're almost to Deersmith.

26:30.489 --> 26:32.059
- Deersmith?

26:32.124 --> 26:34.094
That's where
my grandparents live.

26:34.160 --> 26:36.630
- No shit. Your mom won't be
mad at us for visiting them.

26:36.696 --> 26:38.326
Let's go.
- Oh!

26:38.397 --> 26:40.127
We can visit them?!

26:40.199 --> 26:42.599
- Yeah! Let's go!

26:42.669 --> 26:46.009
- Oh, my goodness,
that would be swell!

26:46.839 --> 26:49.809
- Were you dropped on your head
as a child?

26:50.509 --> 26:52.779
- No. Why?

26:52.845 --> 26:55.405
- Just saying,
the way you talk is so--

26:55.481 --> 26:57.751
- Refined?

26:57.817 --> 26:59.317
- Annoying.

26:59.385 --> 27:01.045
- Oh.

27:02.154 --> 27:07.234
- Hey, we're gonna make
a grandparent pit stop, okay?

27:08.227 --> 27:09.897
- Okay.

27:09.962 --> 27:12.362
- But first the camera.

27:12.431 --> 27:14.501
- Okay.

27:14.566 --> 27:16.466
- Claire...!

27:16.535 --> 27:18.365
(sobbing)

27:24.711 --> 27:27.381
Claire, don't do this to me!

27:32.251 --> 27:33.921
Please...

27:37.256 --> 27:39.386
I'm sorry!!

27:43.095 --> 27:45.255
I'm sorry!

27:45.932 --> 27:49.502
- Okay, now just follow my lead.

27:49.568 --> 27:52.198
- Roger that.

27:52.271 --> 27:54.211
- Yeah.

27:55.574 --> 27:57.014
- Hey.

27:57.076 --> 27:59.046
- Hey. Huh...
- Hey, I called this morning,

27:59.111 --> 28:03.381
and they said that they had
a Canon 310 XL on hold for me.

28:03.449 --> 28:05.319
- Oh, yeah, perfect.

28:05.384 --> 28:06.994
Huh, you're perfect.

28:07.053 --> 28:09.393
That's perfect, that's perfect.

28:09.455 --> 28:11.685
Perfect.

28:11.758 --> 28:13.688
- So can I get it?

28:13.760 --> 28:16.600
- Get what?
- The camera.

28:16.662 --> 28:20.232
- Oh, yeah, we have
a large variety of cameras.

28:20.299 --> 28:22.739
Do you know the brand?
- Canon.

28:22.802 --> 28:25.702
- Okay, Canon. And the model?

28:25.772 --> 28:29.212
- She told you, weirdo.
The 310 XL.

28:29.275 --> 28:33.305
- Oh, yeah, yeah, of course,
of course. One sex.

28:33.379 --> 28:35.109
Second, uh... Sex,

28:35.181 --> 28:37.881
I don't... Wah, if... if only.

28:37.950 --> 28:41.290
I mean, uh...
- Oh, oh... He's bizarro.

28:41.353 --> 28:43.363
- I know. He likes me.

28:43.422 --> 28:45.962
- Well, he shouldn't ignore you,
then.

28:47.593 --> 28:50.503
- Remind me to get you
a personal massager.

28:50.562 --> 28:52.662
- Mom has one of those.

28:52.731 --> 28:53.731
(chuckling)
- No doubt.

28:53.800 --> 28:55.900
- Oh, that's so nice of you.

28:55.968 --> 28:57.738
(sighing)
- Nope.

28:57.804 --> 28:59.344
Uh, sorry.

28:59.405 --> 29:02.975
- What? Uh, she said
they had it this morning.

29:03.042 --> 29:05.242
- Well, sorry, we don't.

29:05.311 --> 29:07.081
- Shit.

29:07.146 --> 29:10.516
- We do have this Beaulieu R8.

29:10.582 --> 29:12.222
- Yeah, how much is that?

29:12.284 --> 29:14.754
- Um, I can give it to you
for 65.

29:14.821 --> 29:17.821
- Fifty.
- I can't. My mom won't let me.

29:17.890 --> 29:19.390
- Aw.

29:19.458 --> 29:22.488
Look, pumpkin,
another home-schooler.

29:23.562 --> 29:26.072
- Okay, fine. Fifty. Cash.

29:26.132 --> 29:28.502
- Great. Fork it over, sister.

29:32.839 --> 29:35.609
And a roll of film. Both: 50.

29:35.674 --> 29:37.544
- I can't. I can't.

29:42.314 --> 29:45.784
Okay. You know, okay, here.
Uh...

29:45.852 --> 29:48.492
(laughing)
- Great. Have a nice day.

29:48.554 --> 29:49.894
- Okay. Two?

29:49.956 --> 29:51.586
I... No?
- Oh! No...

29:51.657 --> 29:53.387
(laughter)

29:54.861 --> 29:56.961
Aren't you gonna ask
for his number?

29:57.029 --> 29:59.869
- Pfft. Man,
I have so much to teach you.

29:59.932 --> 30:02.302
- No, you don't.
Mum's done a great job.

30:02.368 --> 30:04.468
- Yeah.
Let's hit the Raisin Ranch.

30:04.536 --> 30:06.306
- Okay.

30:23.890 --> 30:25.820
Hi.

30:28.861 --> 30:31.101
Uh... hello?

30:33.232 --> 30:36.172
- Greetings,
and welcome to Grasswinds.

30:36.235 --> 30:38.295
- When are your visiting hours?

30:38.370 --> 30:39.840
- 5 to 7.

30:39.906 --> 30:41.636
- Uh, a.m. or p.m.?

30:41.707 --> 30:44.907
- Either way, you're either
too late or too early.

30:44.977 --> 30:48.147
- Uh... we can wait.
- Wait, what?

30:48.214 --> 30:50.384
- You'll wait. We all wait.

30:50.449 --> 30:52.279
- Thank you.

30:54.453 --> 30:55.993
- Hmm.

30:57.924 --> 31:00.034
- We can't wait here that long.

31:00.092 --> 31:02.132
- We're here now.

31:03.930 --> 31:06.230
- Exactly.

31:06.298 --> 31:08.068
Excuse me?

31:10.302 --> 31:11.802
Yo!

31:11.870 --> 31:14.510
- Yes, my darling.

31:14.573 --> 31:16.283
- Do you have a restroom?

31:16.342 --> 31:18.042
- Grasswinds is a place of rest.

31:18.110 --> 31:20.080
We don't isolate it
to one room.

31:20.146 --> 31:23.276
But if you need
to filter your kidneys or...

31:23.349 --> 31:26.589
expunge your bowels,
down the hall, first left.

31:36.128 --> 31:37.628
(sighing contentedly)

31:37.696 --> 31:40.726
- I don't have to go.
- Neither do I.

31:40.799 --> 31:42.729
(music playing)
Look.

31:42.801 --> 31:45.241
- Oh!!

31:45.304 --> 31:48.774
I've never taken
a dance class before.

31:48.840 --> 31:51.610
- Do you see your grandparents?

31:53.579 --> 31:55.249
- No.

31:55.314 --> 31:58.354
I haven't seen them
since I was 12.

31:59.151 --> 32:01.921
- But you'd recognize them,
right?

32:01.988 --> 32:04.088
- Of course.

32:04.156 --> 32:06.826
I send them a picture of me
every birthday

32:06.892 --> 32:09.162
to keep me fresh in their minds.

32:10.462 --> 32:13.732
- Claire? Claire!
- Nana!

32:13.799 --> 32:15.829
- Oh...
- Nana!

32:15.901 --> 32:17.671
Oh!

32:18.604 --> 32:20.914
- Come here, Claire bear!
Come here!

32:20.973 --> 32:24.013
- Pop-Pop!
- Ah...!!

32:25.744 --> 32:29.054
Ah! Oh, look at you!

32:29.115 --> 32:31.275
(laughing)
- But...

32:31.350 --> 32:34.790
Mum said you had dementia
and that you could barely move.

32:34.853 --> 32:36.423
- Really?
- Catherine.

32:36.488 --> 32:39.558
- She has some nerve.
- Remember your exercises.

32:39.625 --> 32:41.155
- Mmm...

32:41.227 --> 32:42.687
Ah!
- What?

32:42.761 --> 32:46.171
- Your mother and I
have entirely different ways

32:46.232 --> 32:49.202
of moving through our journey
of existence.

32:49.268 --> 32:52.398
- Why would she say that
about you?

32:53.239 --> 32:55.709
- It's... complicated.

32:56.508 --> 33:00.078
But... look! Look at you!
I am so glad to see you!

33:00.146 --> 33:02.146
We have so much to talk about.

33:02.214 --> 33:04.954
Honey, there is a beautiful
garden in the back.

33:05.017 --> 33:07.117
Let's talk!
- Oh, that's a great idea.

33:07.186 --> 33:09.356
- Okay, okay!
(laughing)

33:09.421 --> 33:11.161
Oh!

33:11.223 --> 33:12.923
This is my friend,

33:12.991 --> 33:14.631
Danielle.
- Hey.

33:14.693 --> 33:16.703
Listen, I'll let you guys
do your thing.

33:16.762 --> 33:19.602
It sounds like you have a lot
to catch up on.

33:19.665 --> 33:22.465
Plus I need to take footage
of this place.

33:22.534 --> 33:24.844
- Well, thank you, dear,
but be careful.

33:24.903 --> 33:27.543
They don't allow cameras here.

33:27.606 --> 33:29.206
- Oh. Shhh.

33:29.275 --> 33:31.835
(giggling)
- Come on.

33:31.910 --> 33:34.280
- That's my friend.

33:34.346 --> 33:36.946
- She's very nice.

33:37.015 --> 33:38.575
- Danielle, I'm home! Finally.

33:38.650 --> 33:41.890
Sorry, it took longer
than I thought.

33:41.953 --> 33:44.123
(knocking)
Danielle?

33:53.765 --> 33:55.625
(soft music)

33:57.603 --> 33:59.313
(soft music)

34:08.480 --> 34:09.850
(sighing)

34:09.915 --> 34:12.315
(phone chiming)

34:14.886 --> 34:16.886
(soft music)

34:16.955 --> 34:19.155
(birdsong)

34:36.608 --> 34:38.737
- You get this
when you get older.

34:38.810 --> 34:41.080
(sniffling)
Oh, gosh.

34:41.147 --> 34:42.907
Ah...
(sniffling)

34:42.981 --> 34:45.021
Oh...

34:45.083 --> 34:47.092
- Hey.

34:47.152 --> 34:50.523
- Hey.
- You ready to go?

34:51.822 --> 34:53.833
(soft music)

34:58.464 --> 35:01.474
Everything okay?
- She's gonna be just fine.

35:01.533 --> 35:05.303
- You can visit us anytime.
- Anytime.

35:05.371 --> 35:08.741
- I will.
(grandmother chuckling)

35:10.176 --> 35:13.146
(sighing)
- Love to your mother.

35:13.212 --> 35:16.552
- Can we not talk about her,
please?

35:17.416 --> 35:20.546
- Oh, dinner... is on us.

35:21.187 --> 35:23.017
(Claire giggling)

35:23.088 --> 35:25.218
- Thanks, Pop-Pop.

35:27.359 --> 35:28.989
I don't wanna go.

35:29.060 --> 35:31.000
- Oh...
- Honey, we have to go.

35:31.062 --> 35:34.732
They're gonna wonder
where we are at karaoke class.

35:34.800 --> 35:36.570
- Awesome.

35:38.570 --> 35:43.240
- Oh, sunshine...
everything will be just fine.

35:46.212 --> 35:47.952
You keep an eye on her.

35:48.013 --> 35:49.783
- I will.
- Okay.

35:53.219 --> 35:55.589
- Uh, what she said.

36:03.061 --> 36:04.901
- You ready?

36:10.769 --> 36:12.599
(sighing)

36:13.772 --> 36:15.442
(sighing)

36:16.908 --> 36:19.008
(sighing)

36:19.077 --> 36:21.607
So what'd you guys talk about?

36:24.583 --> 36:27.453
- Can we just get out of here,
please?

36:28.787 --> 36:30.457
- Yeah, totally.

36:32.791 --> 36:34.631
Um... where?

36:37.429 --> 36:39.299
- I don't care.

36:40.432 --> 36:42.932
I just can't go home right now.

36:45.103 --> 36:46.813
- Okay.

36:54.280 --> 36:56.380
(sighing)

36:56.448 --> 36:58.478
- Give me strength.

37:28.980 --> 37:31.250
- Yes?
- It's me.

37:31.317 --> 37:33.247
It's Paul.

37:33.319 --> 37:35.849
Is, uh, is Claire home?

37:36.855 --> 37:38.415
- No.

37:38.490 --> 37:41.730
Someone stole my Claire
and my car.

37:41.793 --> 37:44.433
- What are you talking about?

37:44.496 --> 37:46.526
Open the door!

37:52.338 --> 37:54.008
- Ah...

37:56.875 --> 37:58.735
You've aged.

37:58.810 --> 38:00.950
- We both have.

38:03.315 --> 38:05.045
Can I come in?

38:10.989 --> 38:13.489
- I've lost her, haven't I?
- No.

38:13.559 --> 38:15.959
- Then why would she just leave
like that?

38:16.027 --> 38:19.127
- I think that you know
the answer to that.

38:19.197 --> 38:21.767
What did she say when she left?

38:21.833 --> 38:23.773
- She didn't tell me anything.

38:23.835 --> 38:27.135
She just said that she had
a responsibility

38:27.205 --> 38:29.475
to fix some broken camera.

38:29.541 --> 38:31.481
- Danielle.

38:31.543 --> 38:34.683
Look, I am sure
that they'll be back tonight.

38:34.746 --> 38:37.846
And I'll wait with you
until they are.

38:37.916 --> 38:39.746
(kettle whistling)

38:42.053 --> 38:44.123
Let me get that.

38:44.189 --> 38:46.789
- All... all... all we have
is English Breakfast.

38:46.858 --> 38:49.998
- It's... it's good to see you
and I am not here for the tea,

38:50.061 --> 38:51.661
Henrietta.
- Ah...

38:51.730 --> 38:54.200
we have a splash of milk,
thank God.

38:54.265 --> 38:57.665
Claire used all the milk
when she made her muffins--

38:57.736 --> 38:59.636
- Henrietta.
- And, um, sugar.

38:59.705 --> 39:02.235
You still take sugar, right?

39:02.307 --> 39:04.137
- Henrietta. Henrietta.

39:04.209 --> 39:06.749
Everything is gonna be okay.

39:07.946 --> 39:09.776
(soft music)

39:19.591 --> 39:22.231
- So, uh, what'd
your grandparents tell you?

39:22.293 --> 39:24.163
- Enough to make this feel

39:24.229 --> 39:27.469
like this is the best decision
I've ever made.

39:27.533 --> 39:31.843
- Amen, sister.
Anywhere in particular?

39:31.903 --> 39:33.843
- Like I said...

39:33.905 --> 39:35.835
I don't care.
(laughing)

39:35.907 --> 39:39.547
- We'll just go to the next gas
station and take it from there.

39:39.611 --> 39:41.911
- Sounds like a plan.

39:46.117 --> 39:48.117
(crickets chirring)

39:50.622 --> 39:52.062
(bell tinkling)

39:52.123 --> 39:53.863
- Restroom?

39:53.925 --> 39:55.325
- Back there.

39:55.393 --> 39:58.933
- Hey, hey, will you get me
chips, beef jerky and water?

39:58.997 --> 40:01.567
And coffee.
Two creams, no sugar.

40:01.633 --> 40:04.443
- Okay. Oh!

40:04.503 --> 40:06.613
- I might be a while.

40:14.312 --> 40:16.012
Hi.

40:17.483 --> 40:19.153
- Hi.

40:20.486 --> 40:23.886
- You know where you are?
- Now I do.

40:23.955 --> 40:27.055
- Well, that makes one of us.
(laughing)

40:27.125 --> 40:29.955
- There isn't anyone in there,
by the way.

40:30.028 --> 40:32.028
- Oh. Thanks.

40:41.840 --> 40:44.440
- Oh, hey.
- Hey.

40:44.510 --> 40:47.480
- Do you have
any white "Zenvendel"?

40:47.546 --> 40:50.146
- Are you old enough?
- I sure am.

40:50.215 --> 40:52.045
I bought some earlier this week.

40:52.117 --> 40:55.247
- Oh, good for you.
It's in the back left.

40:55.320 --> 40:57.720
- Neato!
(laughing)

41:09.200 --> 41:10.970
- Hey, um...

41:11.036 --> 41:13.636
I'll throw in a couple
of free jerkies

41:13.705 --> 41:15.605
if you eat one real slow.

41:15.674 --> 41:18.044
- Oh, that's so sweet of you.

41:37.028 --> 41:39.768
- How far back can you put it?

41:43.101 --> 41:44.671
(gagging)

41:44.736 --> 41:46.496
Okay, that's enough.

41:46.572 --> 41:49.512
Um, that'll be... 15.75.

41:49.575 --> 41:51.235
- Okay.

41:56.247 --> 41:58.247
One, two,

41:58.316 --> 42:02.516
three, four, five, 15.

42:03.955 --> 42:05.255
Fifty...

42:06.257 --> 42:08.187
Sixty... 85.

42:08.259 --> 42:10.159
You owe me a dime.

42:13.832 --> 42:16.942
Oh.
(giggling)

42:18.269 --> 42:19.769
- Here ya go.

42:19.838 --> 42:22.438
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

42:22.507 --> 42:24.737
- Have a good day.
- You, too.

42:39.457 --> 42:41.157
- Hello.

42:41.226 --> 42:42.826
- Hi.

42:44.596 --> 42:48.196
I'm just waiting for my friend,
but I should probably pee too.

42:48.266 --> 42:51.166
(laughing)
- Yes, you probably should.

42:52.470 --> 42:54.210
- I like your guitar.

42:54.272 --> 42:56.612
- Thank you.
It's a ukulele, actually.

42:56.675 --> 42:59.905
- Oh, it's so cute.
Are you in a band?

42:59.978 --> 43:03.048
- No.
Nah, I'm just doing my thing.

43:03.114 --> 43:07.194
- Me too. Just doing my thing.
(laughing)

43:08.319 --> 43:10.589
Are you lost?

43:10.656 --> 43:12.586
- Sometimes.

43:12.658 --> 43:14.058
- Where you going?

43:14.125 --> 43:16.825
We're going
to the Pump Up the Jamboree.

43:17.663 --> 43:20.803
- No way.
That's where I'm going.

43:20.866 --> 43:22.296
Wh-where is it exactly?

43:22.367 --> 43:23.897
- Ah.

