- I don't even know what I did.

01:04:19.089 --> 01:04:21.629
You're, like, my best friend.

01:04:24.461 --> 01:04:26.231
- Oh, Claire.

01:04:26.296 --> 01:04:29.396
- Oh, Hal, spread me like jelly!

01:04:29.466 --> 01:04:31.396
- What are you watching?

01:04:31.468 --> 01:04:33.598
- Oh... this is amazing.

01:04:34.604 --> 01:04:36.414
(woman moaning)

01:04:36.473 --> 01:04:37.773
- Gross.

01:04:37.841 --> 01:04:40.481
- Yeah, yeah, yeah...

01:04:40.544 --> 01:04:42.384
- What?

01:04:42.446 --> 01:04:45.346
- This is vintage.
Look at her nails.

01:04:45.415 --> 01:04:49.215
- Oh, ho, ho, ho, ho!
- Look at his back.

01:04:49.286 --> 01:04:51.556
- He loves her, doesn't he?

01:04:51.621 --> 01:04:53.991
(woman crying out)

01:04:54.959 --> 01:04:56.729
- Uh, no.

01:04:56.793 --> 01:04:59.003
No, he doesn't.

01:05:00.497 --> 01:05:01.897
- But...

01:05:01.966 --> 01:05:04.066
(indistinct dialogue)

01:05:04.134 --> 01:05:07.904
But...
look what she's letting him do.

01:05:07.972 --> 01:05:10.212
(woman crying out)

01:05:10.640 --> 01:05:12.580
Especially there.

01:05:12.642 --> 01:05:14.582
(woman): Ouch!

01:05:14.644 --> 01:05:17.254
Ah! Oh!

01:05:17.314 --> 01:05:20.584
Are you going to...

01:05:20.650 --> 01:05:23.590
Ah! ...the reunion?!

01:05:23.653 --> 01:05:25.763
Ah! Ooh!

01:05:25.822 --> 01:05:29.562
- Have... you ever done that?

01:05:30.327 --> 01:05:32.457
- Totally.
(man): Oh, yeah.

01:05:32.529 --> 01:05:35.729
* Row row row your boat... **

01:05:35.799 --> 01:05:39.139
- You know, we should probably
think of a plan.

01:05:39.203 --> 01:05:40.973
We're running low on funds.

01:05:41.038 --> 01:05:43.138
Do you have an ATM card?

01:05:43.207 --> 01:05:45.477
- Is that like
a pregnancy thing?

01:05:45.542 --> 01:05:49.882
- No, a bank card.
- No, we're cash only at home.

01:05:49.946 --> 01:05:51.976
Mum doesn't believe
in electronic--

01:05:52.049 --> 01:05:53.779
- Unless they're inside her?

01:05:53.850 --> 01:05:55.250
- What?
- Never mind.

01:05:55.319 --> 01:05:57.349
Seriously, though,
we need a plan.

01:05:57.421 --> 01:06:01.561
- Well... I think
I need to go to Jamboree.

01:06:01.625 --> 01:06:06.095
I mean, I really wanna go
to the Jamboree.

01:06:06.163 --> 01:06:08.503
- Really?
- Yeah!

01:06:12.502 --> 01:06:15.342
- We'll barely make it there,
though,

01:06:15.405 --> 01:06:18.305
and we'll be skimping for food.

01:06:18.375 --> 01:06:21.875
- Well, if the Jews
spent 40 years in a desert,

01:06:21.945 --> 01:06:23.475
I think we'll be fine.

01:06:23.547 --> 01:06:26.317
- Okay, well, what about me?
- What about you?

01:06:26.383 --> 01:06:29.993
- I just get the pleasure
of dropping you off at Jamboree?

01:06:30.054 --> 01:06:31.824
- You can come!

01:06:31.888 --> 01:06:33.618
- Uh...

01:06:33.690 --> 01:06:37.890
- Besides, look how many pins
you'll get to put on your map.

01:06:37.961 --> 01:06:41.901
- That was the map of the world.
We're on Highway 6.

01:06:41.965 --> 01:06:45.635
- But we're more along Highway 6
than we were yesterday.

01:06:45.702 --> 01:06:48.942
- That's a good point. Okay.
Shit, I gotta pay.

01:06:49.005 --> 01:06:51.775
- Oh, suck on a beef jerky
real slow

01:06:51.841 --> 01:06:54.181
and they'll give you a free one.

01:06:54.244 --> 01:06:56.354
- We're at a different station.

01:06:56.413 --> 01:06:58.823
- Oh, I'm pretty sure
it's a universal truth.

01:06:58.882 --> 01:07:02.222
- I'm pretty sure it's not.
- Well, you...

01:07:02.286 --> 01:07:05.286
You should just try it anyway!

01:07:07.657 --> 01:07:09.727
- Okay, alright.

01:07:09.793 --> 01:07:11.663
(Claire laughing)

01:07:11.728 --> 01:07:15.868
Yeah, you're doing it right.
Look through the viewfinder.

01:07:15.932 --> 01:07:19.302
And then focus on your feet.

01:07:20.104 --> 01:07:21.674
And then you'll notice

01:07:21.738 --> 01:07:24.538
that the focus
on the horizon softens.

01:07:24.608 --> 01:07:26.478
- Cool...!

01:07:28.078 --> 01:07:30.648
So what's all this filming for?

01:07:34.784 --> 01:07:36.354
- Oh, nothing.

01:07:36.420 --> 01:07:39.090
- It's not nothing.

01:07:39.156 --> 01:07:41.326
- It's nothing.

01:07:42.892 --> 01:07:46.662
-= My mum says that when truth
is replaced by silence,

01:07:46.730 --> 01:07:48.700
the silence is a lie.

01:07:51.135 --> 01:07:53.335
- Okay, it's for my mom.

01:07:53.403 --> 01:07:55.713
- Oh, that's so nice.

01:07:55.772 --> 01:07:58.112
Where does she live?

01:08:01.678 --> 01:08:03.578
Oh...

01:08:03.647 --> 01:08:08.417
- No, it's okay. I mean,
she died when I was six, y'know?

01:08:08.485 --> 01:08:11.355
She was
in a really bad accident.

01:08:13.157 --> 01:08:14.887
You know, she never...

01:08:14.958 --> 01:08:18.928
got to finish the film
she was making, so...

01:08:18.995 --> 01:08:21.265
I don't know, it's stupid.

01:08:24.167 --> 01:08:26.138
- It's not stupid.

01:08:26.203 --> 01:08:29.542
- I have no idea what I'm doing.

01:08:31.006 --> 01:08:32.837
- Makes two of us.

01:08:42.852 --> 01:08:44.551
- Thanks.

01:08:49.859 --> 01:08:51.529
You wanna check that out?

01:08:51.595 --> 01:08:54.854
- Oh! Uh... yes!
- Yeah?

01:08:58.167 --> 01:09:01.638
- Hey, Henrietta, don't
your folks live around here?

01:09:01.705 --> 01:09:04.765
- Uh... yes.

01:09:04.841 --> 01:09:06.810
- Quick pop-in?

01:09:06.876 --> 01:09:10.145
- Uh... no, thank you.

01:09:10.214 --> 01:09:12.254
- Okay.

01:09:27.397 --> 01:09:29.767
- Hello?
- Hello?!

01:09:31.901 --> 01:09:33.770
Hello?!

01:09:35.071 --> 01:09:37.241
- Can I help you girls?

01:09:37.307 --> 01:09:40.037
- Oh. I'm here for the contest.

01:09:40.109 --> 01:09:43.209
- Are you now?
- Sure am, sir.

01:09:43.279 --> 01:09:48.290
- Well, we don't have karaoke
contest this early on a weekday,

01:09:48.352 --> 01:09:50.452
but that's unfortunate,
'cause, girls,

01:09:50.520 --> 01:09:52.790
I'd love to hear you sing.

01:09:52.856 --> 01:09:56.626
- We should go.
- The stage is all yours.

01:09:57.427 --> 01:10:00.597
I could hum for ya.

01:10:00.664 --> 01:10:02.934
Hmmmmmmm...

01:10:07.271 --> 01:10:09.811
Heeeeh....

01:10:11.641 --> 01:10:13.641
Mm-hmm...

01:10:14.444 --> 01:10:16.884
Hmm-hmm-hmm...
(door closing)

01:10:16.946 --> 01:10:19.246
Hmm... hmm...

01:10:19.316 --> 01:10:21.646
Heeeh...

01:10:27.090 --> 01:10:29.960
- Could you roll the window down
for me, please?

01:10:30.026 --> 01:10:32.896
- Uh, could...
could we keep it up, please?

01:10:32.962 --> 01:10:34.862
- Window down!

01:10:37.634 --> 01:10:39.844
License and registration.

01:10:41.137 --> 01:10:43.237
Everything okay there, ma'am?

01:10:43.307 --> 01:10:44.637
- Oh, yes, she's, uh...
agoraphobic.

01:10:44.708 --> 01:10:47.178
- I won't pretend to know
what that means.

01:10:47.243 --> 01:10:49.513
- I have a great fear
of being in--

01:10:49.579 --> 01:10:52.049
- And I won't pretend to care.

01:10:52.115 --> 01:10:53.715
- Okay...

01:10:53.783 --> 01:10:55.793
- You rolled through that stop,
mister.

01:10:55.852 --> 01:10:58.392
- I did, didn't I?
- You certainly did.

01:10:58.455 --> 01:10:59.885
Bad boy.
- Well, I'm...

01:10:59.956 --> 01:11:03.186
I'm very sorry, Officer.
I'm a man of the cloth and--

01:11:03.259 --> 01:11:05.599
- So why the rolling stop,
Paul?

01:11:05.662 --> 01:11:07.702
- Well, we...
we were preoccupied.

01:11:07.764 --> 01:11:11.944
Our daughters just up and left
this morning and so--

01:11:12.001 --> 01:11:14.241
- Your daughters?
- Uh, well... daughters.

01:11:14.304 --> 01:11:17.614
He has a daughter,
I have a daughter.

01:11:17.674 --> 01:11:19.244
They're separate daughters.

01:11:19.309 --> 01:11:24.309
And... and I have a sense
of where they're heading, uh,

01:11:24.381 --> 01:11:26.221
but, you know,
they could be anywhere.

01:11:26.282 --> 01:11:27.752
- Whose vehicle are they in?

01:11:27.817 --> 01:11:31.047
- They are in mine, Officer.
- Yeah, this is a rental.

01:11:31.120 --> 01:11:33.190
- Oh, there goes my crush.

01:11:34.157 --> 01:11:37.427
Look, give me the license plate
number and I'll put out a call.

01:11:37.494 --> 01:11:42.204
I know some of the motel owners
around here.

01:11:42.265 --> 01:11:44.925
- Oh, okay it's, uh, S4326...

01:11:45.001 --> 01:11:47.671
(engine stalling)

01:11:47.737 --> 01:11:49.307
- Shit.

01:11:49.373 --> 01:11:52.443
Shit. Shit, shit, shit, shit!

01:11:52.509 --> 01:11:55.179
- What?
- Car's dead.

01:11:55.244 --> 01:11:58.984
- Uh... everything will be okay.

01:12:02.386 --> 01:12:03.746
What?

01:12:03.820 --> 01:12:08.060
- I skip town and my dad
only calls me three times?

01:12:09.526 --> 01:12:12.756
I bet your mom's going berserk.

01:12:13.930 --> 01:12:15.870
- Yeah...

01:12:17.401 --> 01:12:19.071
Let her.

01:12:20.737 --> 01:12:24.337
- Okay, according to my phone,
there's a gas station...

01:12:24.408 --> 01:12:26.938
that way a little ways.

01:12:27.944 --> 01:12:29.514
- Should we walk?

01:12:29.579 --> 01:12:32.719
- I'm not going back in there.

01:12:32.782 --> 01:12:34.182
- Okay!

01:12:34.250 --> 01:12:36.590
Wait here one second.

01:12:36.653 --> 01:12:38.793
- Well, it looks
like a Danielle Logan

01:12:38.855 --> 01:12:42.025
checked into the Shady Pines
on Highway 8 last night.

01:12:42.091 --> 01:12:45.261
- That's my girl.
- So let's go check it out.

01:12:45.328 --> 01:12:47.358
Follow me.
- Thank you, thank you.

01:12:47.431 --> 01:12:49.701
Thank you very much.
You see?

01:12:53.102 --> 01:12:55.642
- Oh, cool!

01:12:56.440 --> 01:12:58.210
Look at these!

01:12:58.274 --> 01:13:00.484
(Danielle laughing)

01:13:01.611 --> 01:13:03.551
- Henrietta!

01:13:07.451 --> 01:13:09.751
Oh!
- Oh.

01:13:13.122 --> 01:13:15.592
(giggling)
- What?

01:13:17.827 --> 01:13:19.097
- Here.

01:13:19.162 --> 01:13:21.002
As a thanks.

01:13:36.813 --> 01:13:39.183
Did I do something wrong?

01:13:41.017 --> 01:13:42.517
- No.

01:13:44.020 --> 01:13:45.250
No.

01:13:45.321 --> 01:13:48.891
That was really, really sweet.

01:13:48.958 --> 01:13:50.658
Thank you.

01:13:50.727 --> 01:13:53.527
- That's your favourite, right?

01:13:55.164 --> 01:13:57.174
- My mom used to drink it.

01:13:58.835 --> 01:14:02.105
The smell of the cork
reminds me of her.

01:14:07.410 --> 01:14:09.180
- Well...

01:14:11.180 --> 01:14:13.320
We're finishing her film,

01:14:13.382 --> 01:14:16.122
we should drink it
in her honour.

01:14:16.185 --> 01:14:18.885
- I'm not gonna argue with that.

01:14:21.525 --> 01:14:23.285
This looks good on you.

01:14:23.359 --> 01:14:25.899
- Thanks! I like yours, too.

01:14:28.364 --> 01:14:30.134
(music)

01:14:30.199 --> 01:14:32.569
(indistinct chatter)

01:14:42.912 --> 01:14:46.352
- Yeah, the boy left
around 6 a.m. this morning.

01:14:46.415 --> 01:14:47.915
He seemed kind of stressed.

01:14:47.984 --> 01:14:49.994
Also,
someone owes me some money.

01:14:50.053 --> 01:14:53.323
There's an outstanding charge
for, uh, a "blue" movie.

01:14:53.389 --> 01:14:55.659
- Blue?

01:14:55.725 --> 01:14:58.485
- Pfft. Good girls, I see.
- Yeah.

01:14:58.562 --> 01:15:01.132
- The best. Well, mine is.

01:15:01.197 --> 01:15:03.567
- Which flick?
- Oh, it's a good one.

01:15:03.633 --> 01:15:05.303
Uh, Second Cousin
Twice Removed.

01:15:05.368 --> 01:15:07.998
Classic.

01:15:10.339 --> 01:15:12.639
- What? What?

01:15:12.709 --> 01:15:17.149
There was definitely something
in that look.

01:15:17.213 --> 01:15:19.553
(music)

01:15:19.616 --> 01:15:21.746
(indistinct chatter)

01:15:21.818 --> 01:15:25.118
- Best friends!
(laughter)

01:15:27.323 --> 01:15:29.793
(...music...)

01:15:39.769 --> 01:15:41.969
(...music...)

01:15:59.689 --> 01:16:01.789
(...music...)

01:16:03.459 --> 01:16:05.289
- Whoo!

01:16:11.801 --> 01:16:13.571
(music fading)

01:16:13.637 --> 01:16:15.667
(howling)

01:16:18.174 --> 01:16:19.914
This is...

01:16:19.976 --> 01:16:21.406
(gasping)

01:16:21.477 --> 01:16:24.147
This is so...

01:16:24.213 --> 01:16:25.923
cool!

01:16:25.982 --> 01:16:30.552
- Are you little girls out here
in the forest all by yourselves?

01:16:30.620 --> 01:16:33.020
- Oh, we sure are.

01:16:33.089 --> 01:16:36.129
- Welcome
to the full-moon party.

01:16:36.192 --> 01:16:38.032
(phone ringing)

01:16:39.996 --> 01:16:41.966
Hello?

01:16:42.031 --> 01:16:43.301
So sorry.

01:16:43.366 --> 01:16:45.126
Yeah?

01:16:45.201 --> 01:16:46.941
No, no.

01:16:48.004 --> 01:16:50.674
It's like my one big night.

01:16:51.641 --> 01:16:55.611
We can get whatever's
in the basement out tomorrow.

01:16:55.679 --> 01:16:58.049
Yeah, look, I gotta go.

01:16:59.348 --> 01:17:01.148
So sorry.
(chuckling)

01:17:01.217 --> 01:17:02.747
You guys tripping?

01:17:02.819 --> 01:17:06.959
You have to try
my super-spicy space cakes.

01:17:07.023 --> 01:17:09.993
(music playing)
What's the matter?

01:17:10.059 --> 01:17:12.429
- We're lost
and our car broke down.

01:17:12.495 --> 01:17:13.925
- Claire!

01:17:13.997 --> 01:17:17.197
- That is such a bummer. Where?

01:17:17.266 --> 01:17:18.966
- On our way here, yeah.

01:17:19.035 --> 01:17:21.705
- Look...
here's what needs to happen.

01:17:21.771 --> 01:17:24.441
You need to eat some cake,

01:17:24.507 --> 01:17:26.637
you need to get silly,

01:17:26.710 --> 01:17:28.380
and you need to dance.

01:17:28.444 --> 01:17:31.554
You're totally safe with me.

01:17:32.315 --> 01:17:36.815
Trust me. Seriously,
you girls are in for a treat.

01:17:36.886 --> 01:17:39.386
- Ah... ah...

01:17:40.289 --> 01:17:43.829
Whoa...
(speaking with mouth full)

01:17:43.893 --> 01:17:45.493
That's great.

01:17:45.561 --> 01:17:47.501
- Let's go.
- It is so good.

01:17:47.563 --> 01:17:49.903
- Yeah.
(laughter)

01:17:49.966 --> 01:17:52.996
(beat-heavy music)

01:18:15.324 --> 01:18:18.464
(demonic voice)
(techno music)

01:19:25.829 --> 01:19:28.099
- Now don't freak out.
Don't fall.

01:19:28.164 --> 01:19:30.104
- Ah.
- Okay?

01:19:30.166 --> 01:19:33.436
- Yeah.
- But imagine that wall gone.

01:19:33.502 --> 01:19:35.912
- Oh.
- Mm-hmm.

01:19:35.972 --> 01:19:38.742
Bedroom - bang.

01:19:38.808 --> 01:19:40.978
Upstairs fireplace,

01:19:41.044 --> 01:19:43.414
second bedroom.

01:19:43.479 --> 01:19:45.979
Oh, my fuck,

01:19:46.049 --> 01:19:48.479
his croissants are to die for.

01:19:48.551 --> 01:19:49.991
Must have one now.

01:19:50.053 --> 01:19:52.063
Oh, you're up.

01:19:58.327 --> 01:19:59.727
- 'Morning.

01:19:59.795 --> 01:20:02.465
- Hi.

01:20:02.531 --> 01:20:04.671
- Hello. You're handsome.

01:20:04.733 --> 01:20:07.043
(chuckling)
- I'm Hal.

01:20:07.103 --> 01:20:10.343
- I'm Danielle. This is Claire.

01:20:10.406 --> 01:20:11.976
- We're girls.

01:20:12.041 --> 01:20:15.211
- I can tell. Hungry?

01:20:15.278 --> 01:20:18.208
- Starved.
- Follow me.

01:20:19.148 --> 01:20:21.918
- Mmm...
- We have more if you want.

01:20:21.985 --> 01:20:25.445
- Only if you have more
of this insane jam.

01:20:25.521 --> 01:20:28.821
- Jelly jams!
These are my jelly jams.

01:20:28.892 --> 01:20:30.462
(laughter)

01:20:30.526 --> 01:20:32.596
- Yes! Those are
your little jelly jams.

01:20:32.661 --> 01:20:35.661
- These are my jelly--
- I really like your jelly jams.

01:20:35.731 --> 01:20:38.471
- You like my jelly jams?
- They're really nice ones.

01:20:38.534 --> 01:20:41.504
- I really like your jelly jams.
- Thanks. You do?

01:20:41.570 --> 01:20:43.370
- Mm-hmm.
- Aw...!

01:20:43.439 --> 01:20:45.269
(laughter)

01:20:47.911 --> 01:20:49.581
- The car's been spotted.

01:20:49.645 --> 01:20:52.415
- Oh, wonderful.
- Uh, so we'll follow you, then?

01:20:52.481 --> 01:20:54.651
- No, no, no, we'll take my car.
Leave yours here.

01:20:54.717 --> 01:20:56.287
- Oh, that's very kind of you.

01:20:56.352 --> 01:20:59.522
- It is. But I'm not going
to drive you anywhere

01:20:59.588 --> 01:21:02.758
until you tell me
what's really going on here.

01:21:02.825 --> 01:21:04.625
- Here?

01:21:09.365 --> 01:21:11.195
(water running)
(groaning softly)

01:21:11.267 --> 01:21:13.437
(man): Ahem.
(Claire giggling)

01:21:15.604 --> 01:21:17.214
- Where's Artemis?

01:21:17.273 --> 01:21:19.713
- He's gone
to get your car fixed.

01:21:19.775 --> 01:21:22.145
- Oh, that's wonderful.

01:21:23.279 --> 01:21:25.349
Can I help with anything?

01:21:25.414 --> 01:21:29.054
- Well, uh, you can crack
some eggs over there.

01:21:29.118 --> 01:21:31.588
- Oh, I don't know
how to do that.

01:21:31.654 --> 01:21:33.324
- Seriously?

01:21:34.123 --> 01:21:36.433
- We buy the yolks
in the carton.

01:21:36.492 --> 01:21:39.362
(laughing)
- That is so suburban.

01:21:39.428 --> 01:21:42.568
Uh, come here, let me show you.

01:21:42.631 --> 01:21:44.571
Here we go.

01:21:44.633 --> 01:21:46.643
Okay, grab an egg.

01:21:47.436 --> 01:21:50.666
Okay, bump it just hard enough
to crack the shell,

01:21:50.739 --> 01:21:53.909
but gentle enough
not to damage the egg inside.

01:21:53.977 --> 01:21:56.807
Ready? Okay, now...
